properties.sfomuseum:description: Handwritten letter from Harold M. Bixby to his wife, Debby Bixby, dated Saturday, November 11, [1933], on stationery from the Manila Hotel; includes description of ongoing negotiations for Pan American’s franchise in the Philippines; mentions Salvador Araneta, Judge [James] Ross, Governor General [Frank Murphy] and Benito Buenocamino.
